### In Popular Culture

Elmina Castle's imposing presence and historical weight have made it a compelling backdrop for various media. Scenes from a season 6 episode of the [FX](/FX_(TV_channel)) series [Snowfall](/Snowfall_(TV_series)) were filmed within its walls. The episode's title, "Door of No Return," poignantly references the symbolic gateway through which countless Africans were forced during the slave trade, a fate embodied by castles like Elmina.

The castle also played a significant role in the 2015 Danish film *Guldkysten* ([Gold Coast](/Guldkysten_(film))).

